<LegalLayout title="Privacy Policy" description="How Procrastination Fix collects, uses, retains, and protects personal information." effectiveDate="July 11, 2026">
  <h2>Who We Are</h2>
  <p>Procrastination-fix is a Ghana-based content creator website that provides educational productivity content and recommends third-party services. Procrastination-fix is responsible for deciding why and how personal information submitted directly to us is used.</p>
  <p>Privacy, access, correction, deletion, and other data requests may be sent to <strong>stawelba@gmail.com</strong>.</p>

  <h2>Scope</h2>
  <p>This policy applies to procrastination-fix.com and information you submit through forms linked from the website. The website is intended for people aged 18 and older. It is not directed to children, and we do not knowingly collect personal information from anyone under 18.</p>

  <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Form information:</strong> Your email address, an optional name, and an optional response describing what you would like help with.</li>
    <li><strong>Communications:</strong> Information contained in messages you send to us and our responses.</li>
    <li><strong>Technical information:</strong> Cloudflare may process IP addresses, browser and device information, request details, and security logs when delivering and protecting the website.</li>
    <li><strong>Theme preference:</strong> The website stores your light or dark theme choice in your browser's local storage. This preference remains on your device and is not used for advertising.</li>
    <li><strong>Affiliate referral information:</strong> When you follow an affiliate link, the partner may record referral, device, cookie, signup, or purchase information under its own privacy policy.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How and Why We Use Information</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Responding to requests:</strong> To answer your message, provide requested content, and suggest relevant resources.</li>
    <li><strong>Affiliate promotions:</strong> To send relevant recommendations where you have agreed to receive them. You may opt out at any time.</li>
    <li><strong>Website delivery and security:</strong> To operate, protect, troubleshoot, and prevent misuse of the website.</li>
    <li><strong>Legal compliance:</strong> To maintain necessary records and respond to lawful requests.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Depending on the law that applies to you, these activities are based on your consent, steps taken at your request, our legitimate interest in responding and operating a secure website, or compliance with a legal obligation. Where we rely on consent, you may withdraw it at any time without affecting earlier lawful processing.</p>

  <h2>Affiliate Relationships</h2>
  <p>Procrastination-fix participates or intends to participate in affiliate programmes operated by Focusmate, ClickUp, and Todoist. Our Todoist links are affiliate links. We may earn a commission when you follow an affiliate link and complete a qualifying action, at no additional cost to you.</p>
  <p>We do not give your Google Form responses or email address to these affiliate partners for commission purposes. When you leave our website, the partner independently controls the information it collects.</p>

  <h2>Service Providers and Disclosures</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Google Forms:</strong> Hosts the request form and stores submitted responses on our behalf.</li>
    <li><strong>Cloudflare:</strong> Delivers and protects the website and may process technical and security information.</li>
    <li><strong>Professional and legal recipients:</strong> Information may be disclosed when reasonably necessary to obtain advice, protect rights or safety, investigate misuse, or comply with law.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>We do not sell your submitted personal information or disclose it to third parties for their own direct marketing unless you separately authorize that disclosure.</p>

  <h2>International Processing</h2>
  <p>Google, Cloudflare, and affiliate partners may process information in countries other than Ghana or your country of residence. Those countries may have different privacy laws. Where required, we rely on safeguards offered by the provider and any legally recognized transfer mechanism.</p>

  <h2>Retention</h2>
  <p>We retain Google Form responses and related communications for up to 24 months after your most recent interaction, unless you request deletion earlier or a longer period is reasonably required for legal, security, or recordkeeping purposes.</p>

  <h2>Security</h2>
  <p>We use reasonable administrative and technical safeguards and reputable service providers to protect personal information. No internet transmission or storage system can be guaranteed to be completely secure.</p>

  <h2>Your Choices and Rights</h2>
  <p>Subject to applicable law, you may ask us to provide access, correct information, delete information, restrict or object to processing, provide portable information where applicable, or withdraw consent. Send requests to <strong>stawelba@gmail.com</strong>. We may need to verify your identity. You may also complain to your local privacy regulator; in Ghana, this is the Data Protection Commission.</p>

  <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>We may revise this policy as the website, service providers, or legal requirements change. The updated version will be posted here with a revised effective date.</p>
</LegalLayout>
